examples.en: Her boyfriend dumped her.
The murderer dumped the body in the river.
She dumped him yesterday.
He dumped her body into the sea.
She'll be dumped in a common grave.
He'd dumped the car a mile away.
He has been dumped from the ticket.
I dumped the coffee down the drain.
Raw sewage had been dumped in the river.
The dirty rotter dumped his wife to marry his secretary.
The security inspector upended my bag and dumped everything out.
He's the type of cad who readily bad-mouths every girl who's ever dumped him.
The factory secretly dumped millions of gallons of raw sewage (=that had not been treated) into the Ohio river.
He dumped a bag of groceries on the table.
The truck dumped the garbage in the street.
Merrill dumped her suitcase down in the hall.
Ellie dumped all the photos of her ex-husband.
He had been killed and his body dumped in a pond.
The company dumped him after many years of service.
She dumped her boyfriend when she fell in love with a rich man.
He found a can of beef stew and dumped it in a saucepan to heat.
Appreciable amounts of noxious wastes are dumped into the harbor.
It seemed that Freeman had killed the man, and dumped the body in the lake.
